{{more citations|date=June 2018}} {{Infobox saint | name = Kalfu | feast_day = | venerated_in = [[Haitian Vodou]], [[Folk Catholicism]] | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | titles = | canonized_date = | canonized_place = | canonized_by = | attributes = Rum, gunpowder, red, black, bulls, demons, 7 tree leaves | patronage = Fire, crossroads, misfortune, destruction, sorcery | major_shrine = | suppressed_date = | issues = }}
'''Kalfu''', '''Kalfou''' or '''Carrefour''' (literally ''[[Intersection (road)|crossroads]]'' - see [[crossroads (mythology)|crossroads in mythology]]) is one of the [[petro loa|petro]] aspects of the spirit [[Papa Legba]] in [[Haitian Vodou]]. He is often envisioned as a young man or as a demon; his color is red and he favors [[rum]] infused with [[gunpowder]]. He is often [[syncretism|syncretised]] with [[Satan]].
As his name indicates, he also controls the crossroads and has the power to grant or deny access to all other [[Loa]], or spirits, and he allows the "crossing" of bad [[luck]], deliberate destruction, misfortune, and injustices.<ref>Corbett, Bob. "Haiti: Short List of Loa." Haiti: Short List of Loa. N.p., n.d. Web. 20 Sept. 2013. [http://www2.webster.edu/~corbetre/haiti/voodoo/shortlist.htm Webster.edu]</ref>
