The '''Rasulid Hexaglot''' is a 14th-century glossary written by a Yemeni King, [[Al-Afdal al-Abbas]] (r. 1363–1377), containing words in six languages, [[Arabic]], [[Persian language|Persian]], [[Turkic languages|Turkic]], [[Medieval Greek|Greek]], [[Armenian language|Armenian]], and [[Middle Mongol|Mongolian]].
==Bibliography== * [[Peter_Benjamin_Golden|P. B. Golden]], ed., ''The King’s Dictionary: The Rasūlid Hexaglot – Fourteenth Century Vocabularies in Arabic, Persian, Turkic, Greek, Armenian and Mongol'', tr. T. Halasi- Kun, P. B. Golden, [[Lajos_Ligeti|L. Ligeti]], and E. Schütz, HO VIII/4, Leiden, 2000.
